name: GINZA(tokyo)
description:
GINZA(tokyo)
4000x2690px

銀座, ぎんざ

Ginza. which means 'a town where silver coins are made', is the most developed area for high-end commercial and entertainment districts in Tokyo,
and is also a place where high-end culture and entertainment coexist.
When I arrived in Ginza, the most striking thing to my eyes were the uniform black-dressed people
who were swiftly going under the numerous billboards in department stores and high-end stores for their respective purposes. It seemed to be expressed.

There are currently tens of thousands of crows living in Tokyo,
but as the mountains and plains cut to create forests disappeared,
they permeated the city and coexisted with humans.
